27 // figure out the toolbar area of a DOM attrib list.
28 // By legacy, it is stored as an integer. As of 4.3.0, it is the enumeration value.
29 QString toolBarAreaStringFromDOMAttributes(const CPP::WriteInitialization::DomPropertyMap &attributes) {
30 const DomProperty *pstyle = attributes.value(key: "toolBarArea"_L1);
31 QString result;
32 if (!pstyle)
33 return result;
34 switch (pstyle->kind()) {
35 case DomProperty::Number:
36 result = QLatin1StringView(language::toolbarArea(v: pstyle->elementNumber()));
37 break;
38 case DomProperty::Enum:
39 result = pstyle->elementEnum();
40 break;
41 default:
42 break;
43 }
44 if (!result.startsWith(s: "Qt::"_L1))
45 result.prepend(s: "Qt::"_L1);
46 return result + ", "_L1;
47 }

49 // Write a statement to create a spacer item.
50 void writeSpacerItem(const DomSpacer *node, QTextStream &output) {
51 const QHash<QString, DomProperty *> properties = propertyMap(properties: node->elementProperty());
52 output << language::operatorNew << "QSpacerItem(";
53
54 int w = 0;
55 int h = 0;
56 if (const DomProperty *sh = properties.value(key: "sizeHint"_L1)) {
57 if (const DomSize *sizeHint = sh->elementSize()) {
58 w = sizeHint->elementWidth();
59 h = sizeHint->elementHeight();
60 }
61 }
62 output << w << ", " << h << ", ";
63
64 // size type
65 QString sizeType;
66 if (const DomProperty *st = properties.value(key: "sizeType"_L1)) {
67 const QString value = st->elementEnum();
68 if (value.startsWith(s: "QSizePolicy::"_L1))
69 sizeType = value;
70 else
71 sizeType = "QSizePolicy::"_L1 + value;
72 } else {
73 sizeType = QStringLiteral("QSizePolicy::Expanding");
74 }
75
76 // orientation
77 bool isVspacer = false;
78 if (const DomProperty *o = properties.value(key: "orientation"_L1)) {
79 const QString orientation = o->elementEnum();
80 if (orientation == "Qt::Vertical"_L1 || orientation == "Vertical"_L1)
81 isVspacer = true;
82 }
83 const QString horizType = isVspacer ? "QSizePolicy::Minimum"_L1 : sizeType;
84 const QString vertType = isVspacer ? sizeType : "QSizePolicy::Minimum"_L1;
85 output << language::enumValue(value: horizType) << ", " << language::enumValue(value: vertType) << ')';
86 }

89 // Helper for implementing comparison functions for integers.
90 int compareInt(int i1, int i2) {
91 if (i1 < i2) return -1;
92 if (i1 > i2) return 1;
93 return 0;
94 }

103 static inline bool iconHasStatePixmaps(const DomResourceIcon *i) {
104 return i->hasElementNormalOff() || i->hasElementNormalOn() ||
105 i->hasElementDisabledOff() || i->hasElementDisabledOn() ||
106 i->hasElementActiveOff() || i->hasElementActiveOn() ||
107 i->hasElementSelectedOff() || i->hasElementSelectedOn();
108 }

110 static inline bool isIconFormat44(const DomResourceIcon *i) {
111 return iconHasStatePixmaps(i) || !i->attributeTheme().isEmpty();
112 }
113
114 // Check on properties. Filter out empty legacy pixmap/icon properties
115 // as Designer pre 4.4 used to remove missing resource references.
116 // This can no longer be handled by the code as we have 'setIcon(QIcon())' as well as 'QIcon icon'
117 static bool checkProperty(const CustomWidgetsInfo *customWidgetsInfo,
118 const QString &fileName, const QString &className,
119 const DomProperty *p) {
120 switch (p->kind()) {
121 // ### fixme Qt 7 remove this: Exclude deprecated properties of Qt 5.
122 case DomProperty::Set:
123 if (p->attributeName() == u"features"
124 && customWidgetsInfo->extends(className, baseClassName: "QDockWidget")
125 && p->elementSet() == u"QDockWidget::AllDockWidgetFeatures") {
126 const QString msg = fileName + ": Warning: Deprecated enum value QDockWidget::AllDockWidgetFeatures was encountered."_L1;
127 qWarning(msg: "%s", qPrintable(msg));
128 return false;
129 }
130 break;
131 case DomProperty::Enum:
132 if (p->attributeName() == u"sizeAdjustPolicy"
133 && customWidgetsInfo->extends(className, baseClassName: "QComboBox")
134 && p->elementEnum() == u"QComboBox::AdjustToMinimumContentsLength") {
135 const QString msg = fileName + ": Warning: Deprecated enum value QComboBox::AdjustToMinimumContentsLength was encountered."_L1;
136 qWarning(msg: "%s", qPrintable(msg));
137 return false;
138 }
139 break;
140 case DomProperty::IconSet:
141 if (const DomResourceIcon *dri = p->elementIconSet()) {
142 if (!isIconFormat44(i: dri)) {
143 if (dri->text().isEmpty()) {
144 const QString msg = QString::fromLatin1(ba: "%1: Warning: An invalid icon property '%2' was encountered.")
145 .arg(args: fileName, args: p->attributeName());
146 qWarning(msg: "%s", qPrintable(msg));
147 return false;
148 }
149 }
150 }
151 break;
152 case DomProperty::Pixmap:
153 if (const DomResourcePixmap *drp = p->elementPixmap())
154 if (drp->text().isEmpty()) {
155 const QString msg = QString::fromUtf8(utf8: "%1: Warning: An invalid pixmap property '%2' was encountered.")
156 .arg(args: fileName, args: p->attributeName());
157 qWarning(msg: "%s", qPrintable(msg));
158 return false;
159 }
160 break;
161 default:
162 break;
163 }
164 return true;
165 }
166}

183int FontHandle::compare(const FontHandle &rhs) const
184{
185 const QString family = m_domFont->hasElementFamily() ? m_domFont->elementFamily() : QString();
186 const QString rhsFamily = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementFamily() ? rhs.m_domFont->elementFamily() : QString();
187
188 if (const int frc = family.compare(s: rhsFamily))
189 return frc;
190
191 const int pointSize = m_domFont->hasElementPointSize() ? m_domFont->elementPointSize() : -1;
192 const int rhsPointSize = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementPointSize() ? rhs.m_domFont->elementPointSize() : -1;
193
194 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: pointSize, i2: rhsPointSize))
195 return crc;
196
197 const int bold = m_domFont->hasElementBold() ? (m_domFont->elementBold() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
198 const int rhsBold = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementBold() ? (rhs.m_domFont->elementBold() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
199 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: bold, i2: rhsBold))
200 return crc;
201
202 const int italic = m_domFont->hasElementItalic() ? (m_domFont->elementItalic() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
203 const int rhsItalic = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementItalic() ? (rhs.m_domFont->elementItalic() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
204 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: italic, i2: rhsItalic))
205 return crc;
206
207 const int underline = m_domFont->hasElementUnderline() ? (m_domFont->elementUnderline() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
208 const int rhsUnderline = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementUnderline() ? (rhs.m_domFont->elementUnderline() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
209 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: underline, i2: rhsUnderline))
210 return crc;
211
212 const int weight = m_domFont->hasElementWeight() ? m_domFont->elementWeight() : -1;
213 const int rhsWeight = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementWeight() ? rhs.m_domFont->elementWeight() : -1;
214 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: weight, i2: rhsWeight))
215 return crc;
216
217 const int strikeOut = m_domFont->hasElementStrikeOut() ? (m_domFont->elementStrikeOut() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
218 const int rhsStrikeOut = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementStrikeOut() ? (rhs.m_domFont->elementStrikeOut() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
219 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: strikeOut, i2: rhsStrikeOut))
220 return crc;
221
222 const int kerning = m_domFont->hasElementKerning() ? (m_domFont->elementKerning() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
223 const int rhsKerning = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementKerning() ? (rhs.m_domFont->elementKerning() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
224 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: kerning, i2: rhsKerning))
225 return crc;
226
227 const int antialiasing = m_domFont->hasElementAntialiasing() ? (m_domFont->elementAntialiasing() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
228 const int rhsAntialiasing = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementAntialiasing() ? (rhs.m_domFont->elementAntialiasing() ? 1 : 0) : -1;
229 if (const int crc = compareInt(i1: antialiasing, i2: rhsAntialiasing))
230 return crc;
231
232 const QString styleStrategy = m_domFont->hasElementStyleStrategy() ? m_domFont->elementStyleStrategy() : QString();
233 const QString rhsStyleStrategy = rhs.m_domFont->hasElementStyleStrategy() ? rhs.m_domFont->elementStyleStrategy() : QString();
234
235 if (const int src = styleStrategy.compare(s: rhsStyleStrategy))
236 return src;
237
238 return 0;
239}

262 const QString rhsDisabledOff = rhs.m_domIcon->hasElementDisabledOff() ? rhs.m_domIcon->elementDisabledOff()->text() : QString();

272 const QString rhsActiveOff = rhs.m_domIcon->hasElementActiveOff() ? rhs.m_domIcon->elementActiveOff()->text() : QString();
273 if (const int comp = activeOff.compare(s: rhsActiveOff))
274 return comp;

276 const QString activeOn = m_domIcon->hasElementActiveOn() ? m_domIcon->elementActiveOn()->text() : QString();
277 const QString rhsActiveOn = rhs.m_domIcon->hasElementActiveOn() ? rhs.m_domIcon->elementActiveOn()->text() : QString();
278 if (const int comp = activeOn.compare(s: rhsActiveOn))
279 return comp;

282 const QString rhsSelectedOff = rhs.m_domIcon->hasElementSelectedOff() ? rhs.m_domIcon->elementSelectedOff()->text() : QString();

347void WriteInitialization::LayoutDefaultHandler::acceptLayoutDefault(DomLayoutDefault *node)
348{
349 if (!node)
350 return;
351 if (node->hasAttributeMargin()) {
352 m_state[Margin] |= HasDefaultValue;
353 m_defaultValues[Margin] = node->attributeMargin();
354 }
355 if (node->hasAttributeSpacing()) {
356 m_state[Spacing] |= HasDefaultValue;
357 m_defaultValues[Spacing] = node->attributeSpacing();
358 }
359}
360
361void WriteInitialization::LayoutDefaultHandler::acceptLayoutFunction(DomLayoutFunction *node)
362{
363 if (!node)
364 return;
365 if (node->hasAttributeMargin()) {
366 m_state[Margin] |= HasDefaultFunction;
367 m_functions[Margin] = node->attributeMargin();
368 m_functions[Margin] += "()"_L1;
369 }
370 if (node->hasAttributeSpacing()) {
371 m_state[Spacing] |= HasDefaultFunction;
372 m_functions[Spacing] = node->attributeSpacing();
373 m_functions[Spacing] += "()"_L1;
374 }

377static inline void writeContentsMargins(const QString &indent, const QString &objectName, int value, QTextStream &str)
378{
379 QString contentsMargins;
380 QTextStream(&contentsMargins) << value << ", " << value << ", " << value << ", " << value;
381 writeSetter(indent, varName: objectName, setter: "setContentsMargins"_L1, v: contentsMargins, str);
382 }
383
384void WriteInitialization::LayoutDefaultHandler::writeProperty(int p, const QString &indent, const QString &objectName,
385 const DomPropertyMap &properties, const QString &propertyName, const QString &setter,
386 int defaultStyleValue, bool suppressDefault, QTextStream &str) const
387{
388 // User value
389 if (const DomProperty *prop = properties.value(key: propertyName)) {
390 const int value = prop->elementNumber();
391 // Emulate the pre 4.3 behaviour: The value form default value was only used to determine
392 // the default value, layout properties were always written
393 const bool useLayoutFunctionPre43 = !suppressDefault && (m_state[p] == (HasDefaultFunction|HasDefaultValue)) && value == m_defaultValues[p];
394 if (!useLayoutFunctionPre43) {
395 bool ifndefMac = (!(m_state[p] & (HasDefaultFunction|HasDefaultValue))
396 && value == defaultStyleValue);
397 if (ifndefMac)
398 str << "#ifndef Q_OS_MAC\n";
399 if (p == Margin) { // Use setContentsMargins for numeric values
400 writeContentsMargins(indent, objectName, value, str);
401 } else {
402 writeSetter(indent, varName: objectName, setter, v: value, str);
403 }
404 if (ifndefMac)
405 str << "#endif\n";
406 return;
407 }
408 }
409 if (suppressDefault)
410 return;
411 // get default.
412 if (m_state[p] & HasDefaultFunction) {
413 // Do not use setContentsMargins to avoid repetitive evaluations.
414 writeSetter(indent, varName: objectName, setter, v: m_functions[p], str);
415 return;
416 }
417 if (m_state[p] & HasDefaultValue) {
418 if (p == Margin) { // Use setContentsMargins for numeric values
419 writeContentsMargins(indent, objectName, value: m_defaultValues[p], str);
420 } else {
421 writeSetter(indent, varName: objectName, setter, v: m_defaultValues[p], str);
422 }
423 }
424 return;
425}

428void WriteInitialization::LayoutDefaultHandler::writeProperties(const QString &indent, const QString &varName,
429 const DomPropertyMap &properties, int marginType,
430 bool suppressMarginDefault,
431 QTextStream &str) const {
432 // Write out properties and ignore the ones found in
433 // subsequent writing of the property list.
434 int defaultSpacing = marginType == WriteInitialization::Use43UiFile ? -1 : 6;
435 writeProperty(p: Spacing, indent, objectName: varName, properties, propertyName: "spacing"_L1, setter: "setSpacing"_L1,
436 defaultStyleValue: defaultSpacing, suppressDefault: false, str);
437 // We use 9 as TopLevelMargin, since Designer seem to always use 9.
438 static const int layoutmargins[4] = {-1, 9, 9, 0};
439 writeProperty(p: Margin, indent, objectName: varName, properties, propertyName: "margin"_L1, setter: "setMargin"_L1,
440 defaultStyleValue: layoutmargins[marginType], suppressDefault: suppressMarginDefault, str);
441}

462
463void WriteInitialization::acceptUI(DomUI *node)
464{
465 m_actionGroupChain.push(t: nullptr);
466 m_widgetChain.push(t: nullptr);
467 m_layoutChain.push(t: nullptr);
468
469 if (node->hasAttributeConnectslotsbyname())
470 m_connectSlotsByName = node->attributeConnectslotsbyname();
471
472 if (auto customSlots = node->elementSlots()) {
473 m_customSlots = customSlots->elementSlot();
474 m_customSignals = customSlots->elementSignal();
475 }
476
477 acceptLayoutDefault(node: node->elementLayoutDefault());
478 acceptLayoutFunction(node: node->elementLayoutFunction());
479
480 if (node->elementCustomWidgets())
481 TreeWalker::acceptCustomWidgets(customWidgets: node->elementCustomWidgets());
482
483 if (m_option.generateImplemetation)
484 m_output << "#include <" << m_driver->headerFileName() << ">\n\n";
485
486 m_stdsetdef = true;
487 if (node->hasAttributeStdSetDef())
488 m_stdsetdef = node->attributeStdSetDef();
489
490 const QString className = node->elementClass() + m_option.postfix;
491 m_generatedClass = className;
492
493 const QString varName = m_driver->findOrInsertWidget(ui_widget: node->elementWidget());
494 m_mainFormVarName = varName;
495
496 const QString widgetClassName = node->elementWidget()->attributeClass();
497
498 const QString parameterType = widgetClassName + " *"_L1;
499 m_output << m_option.indent
500 << language::startFunctionDefinition1("setupUi", parameterType, varName, m_option.indent);
501
502 const QStringList connections = m_uic->databaseInfo()->connections();
503 for (const auto &connection : connections) {
504 if (connection == "(default)"_L1)
505 continue;
506
507 const QString varConn = connection + "Connection"_L1;
508 m_output << m_indent << varConn << " = QSqlDatabase::database("
509 << language::charliteral(connection, m_dindent) << ")" << language::eol;
510 }
511
512 acceptWidget(node: node->elementWidget());
513
514 if (!m_buddies.empty())
515 m_output << language::openQtConfig(shortcutConfigKey());
516 for (const Buddy &b : std::as_const(t&: m_buddies)) {
517 const QString buddyVarName = m_driver->widgetVariableName(attributeName: b.buddyAttributeName);
518 if (buddyVarName.isEmpty()) {
519 fprintf(stderr, format: "%s: Warning: Buddy assignment: '%s' is not a valid widget.\n",
520 qPrintable(m_option.messagePrefix()),
521 qPrintable(b.buddyAttributeName));
522 continue;
523 }
524
525 m_output << m_indent << b.labelVarName << language::derefPointer
526 << "setBuddy(" << buddyVarName << ')' << language::eol;
527 }
528 if (!m_buddies.empty())
529 m_output << language::closeQtConfig(shortcutConfigKey());
530
531 if (node->elementTabStops())
532 acceptTabStops(tabStops: node->elementTabStops());
533
534 if (!m_delayedActionInitialization.isEmpty())
535 m_output << "\n" << m_delayedActionInitialization;
536
537 m_output << "\n" << m_indent << language::self
538 << "retranslateUi(" << varName << ')' << language::eol;
539
540 if (node->elementConnections())
541 acceptConnections(connections: node->elementConnections());
542
543 if (!m_delayedInitialization.isEmpty())
544 m_output << "\n" << m_delayedInitialization << "\n";
545
546 if (m_option.autoConnection && m_connectSlotsByName) {
547 m_output << "\n" << m_indent << "QMetaObject" << language::qualifier
548 << "connectSlotsByName(" << varName << ')' << language::eol;
549 }
550
551 m_output << m_option.indent << language::endFunctionDefinition("setupUi");
552
553 if (!m_mainFormUsedInRetranslateUi) {
554 if (language::language() == Language::Cpp) {
555 // Mark varName as unused to avoid compiler warnings.
556 m_refreshInitialization += m_indent;
557 m_refreshInitialization += "(void)"_L1;
558 m_refreshInitialization += varName ;
559 m_refreshInitialization += language::eol;
560 } else if (language::language() == Language::Python) {
561 // output a 'pass' to have an empty function
562 m_refreshInitialization += m_indent;

880void WriteInitialization::acceptLayout(DomLayout *node)
881{
882 const QString className = node->attributeClass();
883 const QString varName = m_driver->findOrInsertLayout(ui_layout: node);
884
885 const DomPropertyMap properties = propertyMap(properties: node->elementProperty());
886 const bool oldLayoutProperties = properties.value(key: "margin"_L1) != nullptr;
887
888 bool isGroupBox = false;
889
890 m_output << m_indent << varName << " = " << language::operatorNew << className << '(';
891
892 if (!m_layoutChain.top() && !isGroupBox)
893 m_output << m_driver->findOrInsertWidget(ui_widget: m_widgetChain.top());
894
895 m_output << ")" << language::eol;
896
897 // Suppress margin on a read child layout
898 const bool suppressMarginDefault = m_layoutChain.top();
899 int marginType = Use43UiFile;
900 if (oldLayoutProperties)
901 marginType = m_layoutMarginType;
902 m_LayoutDefaultHandler.writeProperties(indent: m_indent, varName, properties, marginType, suppressMarginDefault, str&: m_output);
903
904 m_layoutMarginType = SubLayoutMargin;
905
906 DomPropertyList propList = node->elementProperty();
907 DomPropertyList newPropList;
908 if (m_layoutWidget) {
909 bool left, top, right, bottom;
910 left = top = right = bottom = false;
911 for (const DomProperty *p : propList) {
912 const QString propertyName = p->attributeName();
913 if (propertyName == "leftMargin"_L1 && p->kind() == DomProperty::Number)
914 left = true;
915 else if (propertyName == "topMargin"_L1 && p->kind() == DomProperty::Number)
916 top = true;
917 else if (propertyName == "rightMargin"_L1 && p->kind() == DomProperty::Number)
918 right = true;
919 else if (propertyName == "bottomMargin"_L1 && p->kind() == DomProperty::Number)
920 bottom = true;
921 }
922 if (!left) {
923 DomProperty *p = new DomProperty();
924 p->setAttributeName("leftMargin"_L1);
925 p->setElementNumber(0);
926 newPropList.append(t: p);
927 }
928 if (!top) {
929 DomProperty *p = new DomProperty();
930 p->setAttributeName("topMargin"_L1);
931 p->setElementNumber(0);
932 newPropList.append(t: p);
933 }
934 if (!right) {
935 DomProperty *p = new DomProperty();
936 p->setAttributeName("rightMargin"_L1);
937 p->setElementNumber(0);
938 newPropList.append(t: p);
939 }
940 if (!bottom) {
941 DomProperty *p = new DomProperty();
942 p->setAttributeName("bottomMargin"_L1);
943 p->setElementNumber(0);
944 newPropList.append(t: p);
945 }
946 m_layoutWidget = false;
947 }
948
949 propList.append(l: newPropList);
950
951 writeProperties(varName, className, lst: propList, flags: WritePropertyIgnoreMargin|WritePropertyIgnoreSpacing);
952
953 // Clean up again:
954 propList.clear();
955 qDeleteAll(c: newPropList);
956 newPropList.clear();
957
958 m_layoutChain.push(t: node);
959 TreeWalker::acceptLayout(layout: node);
960 m_layoutChain.pop();
961
962 // Stretch? (Unless we are compiling for UIC3)
963 const QString numberNull(u'0');
964 writePropertyList(varName, setFunction: "setStretch"_L1, value: node->attributeStretch(), defaultValue: numberNull);
965 writePropertyList(varName, setFunction: "setRowStretch"_L1, value: node->attributeRowStretch(), defaultValue: numberNull);
966 writePropertyList(varName, setFunction: "setColumnStretch"_L1, value: node->attributeColumnStretch(), defaultValue: numberNull);
967 writePropertyList(varName, setFunction: "setColumnMinimumWidth"_L1, value: node->attributeColumnMinimumWidth(), defaultValue: numberNull);
968 writePropertyList(varName, setFunction: "setRowMinimumHeight"_L1, value: node->attributeRowMinimumHeight(), defaultValue: numberNull);
969}

1132 switch (language::language()) {
1133 case Language::Cpp:
1134 str << "QStringList{";
1135 break;
1136 case Language::Python:
1137 str << '[';
1138 trailingDelimiter = ']';
1139 break;
1140 }
1141 const QStringList values = list->elementString();
1142 if (!values.isEmpty()) {
1143 if (needsTranslation(element: list)) {
1144 const QString comment = list->attributeComment();
1145 const qsizetype last = values.size() - 1;
1146 for (qsizetype i = 0; i <= last; ++i) {
1147 str << '\n' << m_indent << " " << trCall(str: values.at(i), comment);
1148 if (i != last)
1149 str << ',';
1150 }
1151 } else {
1152 for (qsizetype i = 0; i < values.size(); ++i) {
1153 if (i)
1154 str << ", ";
1155 str << language::qstring(values.at(i), m_dindent);
1156 }
1157 }
1158 }
1159 str << trailingDelimiter;
1160 return propertyValue;
1161}

1769QString WriteInitialization::writeIconProperties(const DomResourceIcon *i)
1770{
1771 // check cache
1772 const IconHandle iconHandle(i);
1773 const IconPropertiesNameMap::const_iterator it = m_iconPropertiesNameMap.constFind(key: iconHandle);
1774 if (it != m_iconPropertiesNameMap.constEnd())
1775 return it.value();
1776
1777 // insert with new name
1778 const QString iconName = m_driver->unique(instanceName: "icon"_L1);
1779 m_iconPropertiesNameMap.insert(key: IconHandle(i), value: iconName);
1780
1781 const bool isCpp = language::language() == Language::Cpp;
1782
1783 if (Q_UNLIKELY(!isIconFormat44(i))) { // pre-4.4 legacy
1784 m_output << m_indent;
1785 if (isCpp)
1786 m_output << "const QIcon ";
1787 m_output << iconName << " = " << pixCall(type: "QIcon"_L1, text: i->text())
1788 << language::eol;
1789 return iconName;
1790 }
1791
1792 // 4.4 onwards
1793 if (i->attributeTheme().isEmpty()) {
1794 // No theme: Write resource icon as is
1795 m_output << m_indent << language::stackVariable("QIcon", iconName)
1796 << language::eol;
1797 if (m_uic->pixmapFunction().isEmpty())
1798 writeResourceIcon(output&: m_output, iconName, indent: m_indent, i);
1799 else
1800 writePixmapFunctionIcon(output&: m_output, iconName, indent: m_indent, i);
1801 return iconName;
1802 }
1803
1804 // Theme: Generate code to check the theme and default to resource
1805 if (iconHasStatePixmaps(i)) {
1806 // Theme + default state pixmaps:
1807 // Generate code to check the theme and default to state pixmaps
1808 m_output << m_indent << language::stackVariable("QIcon", iconName) << language::eol;
1809 const char themeNameStringVariableC[] = "iconThemeName";
1810 // Store theme name in a variable
1811 m_output << m_indent;
1812 if (m_firstThemeIcon) { // Declare variable string
1813 if (isCpp)
1814 m_output << "QString ";
1815 m_firstThemeIcon = false;
1816 }
1817 m_output << themeNameStringVariableC << " = "
1818 << language::qstring(i->attributeTheme()) << language::eol;
1819 m_output << m_indent << "if ";
1820 if (isCpp)
1821 m_output << '(';
1822 m_output << "QIcon" << language::qualifier << "hasThemeIcon("
1823 << themeNameStringVariableC << ')' << (isCpp ? ") {" : ":") << '\n'
1824 << m_dindent << iconName << " = QIcon" << language::qualifier << "fromTheme("
1825 << themeNameStringVariableC << ')' << language::eol
1826 << m_indent << (isCpp ? "} else {" : "else:") << '\n';
1827 if (m_uic->pixmapFunction().isEmpty())
1828 writeResourceIcon(output&: m_output, iconName, indent: m_dindent, i);
1829 else
1830 writePixmapFunctionIcon(output&: m_output, iconName, indent: m_dindent, i);
1831 if (isCpp)
1832 m_output << m_indent << '}';
1833 m_output << '\n';
1834 return iconName;
1835 }
1836
1837 // Theme, but no state pixmaps: Construct from theme directly.
1838 m_output << m_indent
1839 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QIcon", iconName)
1840 << "QIcon" << language::qualifier << "fromTheme("
1841 << language::qstring(i->attributeTheme()) << "))"
1842 << language::eol;
1843 return iconName;
1844}

1905// Write initialization for brush unless it is found in the cache. Returns the name to use
1906// in an expression.
1907QString WriteInitialization::writeBrushInitialization(const DomBrush *brush)
1908{
1909 // Simple solid, colored brushes are cached
1910 const bool solidColoredBrush = !brush->hasAttributeBrushStyle() || brush->attributeBrushStyle() == "SolidPattern"_L1;
1911 uint rgb = 0;
1912 if (solidColoredBrush) {
1913 if (const DomColor *color = brush->elementColor()) {
1914 rgb = ((color->elementRed() & 0xFF) << 24) |
1915 ((color->elementGreen() & 0xFF) << 16) |
1916 ((color->elementBlue() & 0xFF) << 8) |
1917 ((color->attributeAlpha() & 0xFF));
1918 const ColorBrushHash::const_iterator cit = m_colorBrushHash.constFind(key: rgb);
1919 if (cit != m_colorBrushHash.constEnd())
1920 return cit.value();
1921 }
1922 }
1923 // Create and enter into cache if simple
1924 const QString brushName = m_driver->unique(instanceName: "brush"_L1);
1925 writeBrush(brush, brushName);
1926 if (solidColoredBrush)
1927 m_colorBrushHash.insert(key: rgb, value: brushName);
1928 return brushName;
1929}

1931void WriteInitialization::writeBrush(const DomBrush *brush, const QString &brushName)
1932{
1933 QString style = u"SolidPattern"_s;
1934 if (brush->hasAttributeBrushStyle())
1935 style = brush->attributeBrushStyle();
1936
1937 if (style == "LinearGradientPattern"_L1 ||
1938 style == "RadialGradientPattern"_L1 ||
1939 style == "ConicalGradientPattern"_L1) {
1940 const DomGradient *gradient = brush->elementGradient();
1941 const QString gradientType = gradient->attributeType();
1942 const QString gradientName = m_driver->unique(instanceName: "gradient"_L1);
1943 if (gradientType == "LinearGradient"_L1) {
1944 m_output << m_indent
1945 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QLinearGradient", gradientName)
1946 << gradient->attributeStartX()
1947 << ", " << gradient->attributeStartY()
1948 << ", " << gradient->attributeEndX()
1949 << ", " << gradient->attributeEndY() << ')' << language::eol;
1950 } else if (gradientType == "RadialGradient"_L1) {
1951 m_output << m_indent
1952 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QRadialGradient", gradientName)
1953 << gradient->attributeCentralX()
1954 << ", " << gradient->attributeCentralY()
1955 << ", " << gradient->attributeRadius()
1956 << ", " << gradient->attributeFocalX()
1957 << ", " << gradient->attributeFocalY() << ')' << language::eol;
1958 } else if (gradientType == "ConicalGradient"_L1) {
1959 m_output << m_indent
1960 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QConicalGradient", gradientName)
1961 << gradient->attributeCentralX()
1962 << ", " << gradient->attributeCentralY()
1963 << ", " << gradient->attributeAngle() << ')' << language::eol;
1964 }
1965
1966 m_output << m_indent << gradientName << ".setSpread(QGradient"
1967 << language::qualifier << gradient->attributeSpread()
1968 << ')' << language::eol;
1969
1970 if (gradient->hasAttributeCoordinateMode()) {
1971 m_output << m_indent << gradientName << ".setCoordinateMode(QGradient"
1972 << language::qualifier << gradient->attributeCoordinateMode()
1973 << ')' << language::eol;
1974 }
1975
1976 const auto &stops = gradient->elementGradientStop();
1977 for (const DomGradientStop *stop : stops) {
1978 const DomColor *color = stop->elementColor();
1979 m_output << m_indent << gradientName << ".setColorAt("
1980 << stop->attributePosition() << ", "
1981 << domColor2QString(c: color) << ')' << language::eol;
1982 }
1983 m_output << m_indent
1984 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QBrush", brushName)
1985 << gradientName << ')' << language::eol;
1986 } else if (style == "TexturePattern"_L1) {
1987 const DomProperty *property = brush->elementTexture();
1988 const QString iconValue = iconCall(prop: property);
1989
1990 m_output << m_indent
1991 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QBrush", brushName)
1992 << iconValue << ')' << language::eol;
1993 } else {
1994 const DomColor *color = brush->elementColor();
1995 m_output << m_indent
1996 << language::stackVariableWithInitParameters("QBrush", brushName)
1997 << domColor2QString(c: color) << ')' << language::eol;
1998
1999 m_output << m_indent << brushName << ".setStyle("
2000 << language::qtQualifier << style << ')' << language::eol;
2001 }
2002}

2049QString WriteInitialization::pixCall(const DomProperty *p) const
2050{

2055 type = "QIcon"_L1;

2057 break;

2064 qPrintable(m_option.messagePrefix()));
2065 return "QIcon()"_L1;
2066 break;
2067 }
2068 return pixCall(type, text: s);

2072{

2150/*
2151 * Initializers are just strings containing the function call and need to be prepended
2152 * the line indentation and the object they are supposed to initialize.
2153 * String initializers come with a preprocessor conditional (ifdef), so the code
2154 * compiles with QT_NO_xxx. A null pointer means no conditional. String initializers
2155 * are written to the retranslateUi() function, others to setupUi().
2156 */
2157
2158
2159/*!
2160 Create non-string inititializer.
2161 \param value the value to initialize the attribute with. May be empty, in which case
2162 the initializer is omitted.
2163 See above for other parameters.
2164*/
2165void WriteInitialization::addInitializer(Item *item,
2166 const QString &name, int column, const QString &value, const QString &directive, bool translatable) const
2167{
2168 if (!value.isEmpty()) {
2169 QString setter;
2170 QTextStream str(&setter);
2171 str << language::derefPointer << "set" << name.at(i: 0).toUpper() << QStringView{name}.mid(pos: 1) << '(';
2172 if (column >= 0)
2173 str << column << ", ";
2174 str << value << ");";
2175 item->addSetter(setter, directive, translatable);
2176 }
2177}
2178
2179/*!
2180 Create string inititializer.
2181 \param initializers in/out list of inializers
2182 \param properties map property name -> property to extract data from
2183 \param name the property to extract
2184 \param col the item column to generate the initializer for. This is relevant for
2185 tree widgets only. If it is -1, no column index will be generated.
2186 \param ifdef preprocessor symbol for disabling compilation of this initializer
2187*/
2188void WriteInitialization::addStringInitializer(Item *item,
2189 const DomPropertyMap &properties, const QString &name, int column, const QString &directive) const
2190{
2191 if (const DomProperty *p = properties.value(key: name)) {
2192 DomString *str = p->elementString();
2193 QString text = toString(str);
2194 if (!text.isEmpty()) {
2195 bool translatable = needsTranslation(element: str);
2196 QString value = autoTrCall(str);
2197 addInitializer(item, name, column, value, directive, translatable);
2198 }
2199 }
2200}

2344/*!
2345 Create and write out initializers for tree widget items.
2346 This function makes sure that only needed items are fetched (subject to preprocessor
2347 conditionals), that each item is fetched from its parent widget/item exactly once
2348 and that no temporary variables are created for items that are needed only once. As
2349 fetches are built top-down from the root, but determining how often and under which
2350 conditions an item is needed needs to be done bottom-up, the whole process makes
2351 two passes, storing the intermediate result in a recursive StringInitializerListMap.
2352*/
2353WriteInitialization::Items WriteInitialization::initializeTreeWidgetItems(const QList<DomItem *> &domItems)
2354{
2355 // items
2356 Items items;
2357 const int numDomItems = domItems.size();
2358 items.reserve(size: numDomItems);
2359
2360 for (int i = 0; i < numDomItems; ++i) {
2361 const DomItem *domItem = domItems.at(i);
2362
2363 Item *item = new Item("QTreeWidgetItem"_L1, m_indent, m_output, m_refreshOut, m_driver);
2364 items << item;
2365
2366 QHash<QString, DomProperty *> map;
2367
2368 int col = -1;
2369 const DomPropertyList properties = domItem->elementProperty();
2370 for (DomProperty *p : properties) {
2371 if (p->attributeName() == "text"_L1) {
2372 if (!map.isEmpty()) {
2373 addCommonInitializers(item, properties: map, column: col);
2374 map.clear();
2375 }
2376 col++;
2377 }
2378 map.insert(key: p->attributeName(), value: p);
2379 }
2380 addCommonInitializers(item, properties: map, column: col);
2381 // AbstractFromBuilder saves flags last, so they always end up in the last column's map.
2382 addQtFlagsInitializer(item, properties: map, name: "flags"_L1);
2383
2384 const auto subItems = initializeTreeWidgetItems(domItems: domItem->elementItem());
2385 for (Item *subItem : subItems)
2386 item->addChild(child: subItem);
2387 }
2388 return items;

2593ConnectionSyntax WriteInitialization::connectionSyntax(const language::SignalSlot &sender,
2594 const language::SignalSlot &receiver) const
2595{
2596 if (m_option.forceMemberFnPtrConnectionSyntax)
2597 return ConnectionSyntax::MemberFunctionPtr;
2598 if (m_option.forceStringConnectionSyntax)
2599 return ConnectionSyntax::StringBased;
2600 // Auto mode: Use Qt 5 connection syntax for Qt classes and parameterless
2601 // connections. QAxWidget is special though since it has a fake Meta object.
2602 static const QStringList requiresStringSyntax{QStringLiteral("QAxWidget")};
2603 if (requiresStringSyntax.contains(str: sender.className)
2604 || requiresStringSyntax.contains(str: receiver.className)) {
2605 return ConnectionSyntax::StringBased;
2606 }
2607
2608 // QTBUG-110952, ambiguous overloads of display()
2609 if (receiver.className == u"QLCDNumber" && receiver.signature.startsWith(s: u"display("))
2610 return ConnectionSyntax::StringBased;
2611
2612 if ((sender.name == m_mainFormVarName && m_customSignals.contains(str: sender.signature))
2613 || (receiver.name == m_mainFormVarName && m_customSlots.contains(str: receiver.signature))) {
2614 return ConnectionSyntax::StringBased;
2615 }
2616
2617 return sender.signature.endsWith(s: "()"_L1)
2618 || (!isCustomWidget(className: sender.className) && !isCustomWidget(className: receiver.className))
2619 ? ConnectionSyntax::MemberFunctionPtr : ConnectionSyntax::StringBased;
2620}

2622void WriteInitialization::acceptConnection(DomConnection *connection)
2623{
2624 const QString senderName = connection->elementSender();
2625 const QString receiverName = connection->elementReceiver();
2626
2627 const auto senderDecl = findDeclaration(name: senderName);
2628 const auto receiverDecl = findDeclaration(name: receiverName);
2629
2630 if (senderDecl.name.isEmpty() || receiverDecl.name.isEmpty()) {
2631 QString message;
2632 QTextStream(&message) << m_option.messagePrefix()
2633 << ": Warning: Invalid signal/slot connection: \""
2634 << senderName << "\" -> \"" << receiverName << "\".";
2635 fprintf(stderr, format: "%s\n", qPrintable(message));
2636 return;
2637 }
2638 const QString senderSignature = connection->elementSignal();
2639 language::SignalSlotOptions signalOptions;
2640 if (m_uic->customWidgetsInfo()->isAmbiguousSignal(className: senderDecl.className, signalSignature: senderSignature))
2641 signalOptions.setFlag(flag: language::SignalSlotOption::Ambiguous);
2642
2643 language::SignalSlot theSignal{.name: senderDecl.name, .signature: senderSignature,
2644 .className: senderDecl.className, .options: signalOptions};
2645 language::SignalSlot theSlot{.name: receiverDecl.name, .signature: connection->elementSlot(),
2646 .className: receiverDecl.className, .options: {}};
2647
2648 m_output << m_indent;
2649 language::formatConnection(str&: m_output, sender: theSignal, receiver: theSlot,
2650 connectionSyntax: connectionSyntax(sender: theSignal, receiver: theSlot));
2651 m_output << language::eol;
2652}

2654static void generateMultiDirectiveBegin(QTextStream &outputStream, const QSet<QString> &directives)
2655{
2656 if (directives.isEmpty())
2657 return;
2658
2659 if (directives.size() == 1) {
2660 outputStream << language::openQtConfig(*directives.cbegin());
2661 return;
2662 }
2663
2664 auto list = directives.values();
2665 // sort (always generate in the same order):
2666 std::sort(first: list.begin(), last: list.end());
2667
2668 outputStream << "#if " << language::qtConfig(list.constFirst());
2669 for (int i = 1, size = list.size(); i < size; ++i)
2670 outputStream << " || " << language::qtConfig(list.at(i));
2671 outputStream << Qt::endl;
2672}
2673
2674static void generateMultiDirectiveEnd(QTextStream &outputStream, const QSet<QString> &directives)
2675{
2676 if (directives.isEmpty())
2677 return;
2678
2679 outputStream << "#endif" << Qt::endl;
2680}

2699{
2700 if (emptyItemPolicy == Item::DontConstruct && m_setupUiData.policy == ItemData::DontGenerate)

2704 if (emptyItemPolicy == Item::ConstructItemOnly && m_children.isEmpty()) {
2705 if (m_setupUiData.policy == ItemData::DontGenerate) {
2706 m_setupUiStream << m_indent << language::operatorNew << m_itemClassName
2707 << '(' << parent << ')' << language::eol;

2711 generateMultiDirective = true;

2718 m_setupUiStream << m_indent;
2719 if (language::language() == Language::Cpp)
2720 m_setupUiStream << m_itemClassName << " *";
2721 m_setupUiStream << uniqueName
2722 << " = " << language::operatorNew << m_itemClassName << '(' << parent
2723 << ')' << language::eol;

2726 m_setupUiStream << "#else\n";
2727 m_setupUiStream << m_indent << language::operatorNew << m_itemClassName
2728 << '(' << parent << ')' << language::eol;
